    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured person evacuated to Aims Clinic in Houma, LA",
      "First-aid treatment provided on site",
      "Shore-based physician evaluation conducted",
      "BSEE investigation initiated",
      "Daily reports, pictures, witness statements, work permits, and procedures requested"
    ],
    "summary": "On November 23, 2020 at approximately 07:30 hours, a subsea personnel was struck by a 91 lb test cap that fell 2 feet from a gooseneck on the Well Test Deck of the Transocean Deepwater Proteus drillship during drilling operations in Mississippi Canyon 392. The worker was attempting to fit a Choke and Kill test cap onto a gooseneck with assistance from a come-along hoist. The cap came loose due to chain shifting as tension increased, striking the worker's right thumb and causing a distal thumb fracture requiring surgical repair.",
    "recommendations": [],
